"The African Union strongly supports her candidacy and calls on member states and friends of the continent to vote for her," he said in a statement. Okonjo-Iweala and South Korean Trade Minister, Yoo Myung-hee, are final two candidates - from an initial list of eight. The Nigerian would be the first African to be Director General of the WTO. She has had two spells as Finance Minister and a short stint as Foreign Minister in Nigeria --BBC--